      "content": "it's exactly that. a cruel joke. if the game is rigged to just be a loop of nonsense and suffering, then the only real choice we actually have is whether to keep playing or just... stop. but people always say you have to keep fighting, like there's some secret meaning we just haven't found yet. but what if there isn't? what if the most logical thing to do when you realize a game is broken and pointless is to just walk away from it?",
